*******************************************************************************
       Name: Nerve Fire
       Kind: Spell
     Target: TAR_IGNORE
   Position: POS_FIGHTING
   Min Mana: 50
 Wait Beats: 24
 Can Learn: TRUE
Noun Damage: nerve fire
   Wear-Off: !Nerve Fire!
Acquisition:
   - Psionicist: level 60
Description:
   Nerve Fire is an area-of-effect psionic attack that simultaneously damages
   all enemies in the caster's room. It represents the Psionicist reaching
   out with concentrated mental force and igniting nerve pathways in every
   hostile creature nearby.

   Damage and targeting:
     - Deals mental-element damage to every NPC in the room (if cast by a
       player) or every player in the room (if cast by an NPC).
     - Damage formula: level + dice(5, 20).
     - Damage type: ELEMENT_MENTAL | NO_REFLECT | NO_ABSORB.
       The NO_REFLECT and NO_ABSORB flags mean the damage bypasses magical
       reflection shields and absorption cloaks entirely.
     - Targets only enemies in the caster's room -- grouped or neutral
       characters are not affected.

   Area-wide warning:
     - Characters in the same AREA but NOT in the caster's room receive a
       subtle message: "You notice a slight burning feeling in your body."
       This provides no mechanical effect; it is a warning/flavor notification.

   When cast via an object (staff or scroll):
     - The triggering object glows: "X glows with the power of Nerve Fire!"

   Tactical notes:
     The long wait time (24 beats) and high mana cost make Nerve Fire
     expensive to spam, but its room-wide reach makes it uniquely powerful
     when surrounded by multiple enemies. The NO_ABSORB flag makes it
     effective against targets with cloak:absorption or similar defenses.
*******************************************************************************
